pull_request.title: Solve '-Wstrict-prototypes' for clang >= 15.0
pull_request.body:
Since clang 15, the warning '[-Wstrict-prototypes](https://github.com/thb-sb/liboqs/pull/new/fix_Wstrict_prototypes_clang_15)' is now triggered by a missing
prototype in a declaration. For example:

```c
int foo() {
}
```

triggers the warning '-Wstrict-prototypes', because `foo` needs a prototype:

```c
int foo(void) {
}
```

liboqs do have several functions without prototypes. Since clang 15, it breaks
the compilation.

This PR adds the `void` parameter for functions without arguments.

Note: this warning is not enabled by GCC.

pull_request.title: Ensure build without an executable stack (fixes #1285)
pull_request.body:
Until it is clear why the shared library on mips64el and hppa is built with the executable bit set for the stack, build with both `-Wa,--noexecstack` (for the assembler) and `-Wl,-z,--noexecstack` (for the linker).

I can confirm that with this change liboqs 0.7.2 builds on mips64el.

* [no] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [no] Does this PR change the the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming? Does this PR otherwise change an API? (If so, PRs in [oqs-provider](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-provider), [OQS-OpenSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl), [OQS-BoringSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/boringssl), and [OQS-OpenSSH](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssh) will also need to be ready for review and merge by the time this is merged.)
